<span style="font-weight: 400;">Approximately, ulcer affects 1 in every 429 people in the world. The ulcer can develop at any stage, but people between the ages of 15-25 have a higher risk of having one.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Globally, and according to research, ulcerative colitis is more prevalent among whites (European background) and Africans.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">People from Asia background have fewer chances of having one. Considering gender-wise distribution, ulcers are equally prevalent in both men and women.</span>

<b>The ulcer can lead to the following:</b>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Frequent diarrhea which usually contains blood or mucus.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Abdominal pain</span></li>
